de.mrapp.android.adapter.expandablelist

Interface ExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>

  • Type Parameters:
    GroupType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's group items
    ChildType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's child items
    All Superinterfaces:
    Adapter<android.widget.ExpandableListView>, java.lang.Cloneable, DataStructure, EnableStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ExpandableGridViewAdapter, android.widget.ExpandableListAdapter, ExpandableRecyclerViewAdapter, FilterableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, android.widget.HeterogeneousExpandableList, ItemStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, Loggable, Parameterizable, Restorable, java.io.Serializable, SortableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, NoChoiceExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, SelectableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, SingleChoiceExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSelectableExpandableListAdapter, ExpandableListAdapterImplementation, MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapterImplementation, SingleChoiceExpandableListAdapterImplementation

    public interface ExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
extends ExpandableRecyclerViewAdapter, android.widget.ExpandableListAdapter, android.widget.HeterogeneousExpandableList, EnableStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ItemStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, SortableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, FilterableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    Defines the interface, an adapter, whose underlying data is managed as a list of arbitrary group and child items, must implement. Such an adapter's purpose is to provide the underlying data for visualization using a ExpandableListView widget.
    Since:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Michael Rapp
